nt Maduro, the use of military force is not being ruled out."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"&#x201C;When we say all options are on the table, that is because all options are on the table,&#x201D; Abrams said, adding that military force &#x201C;is not the preferred route and not the route we&#x2019;re going down.&#x201D;"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The comments on Capitol Hill by Abrams came as President Trump met in the Oval Office with Colombian President Ivan Duque. The two leaders discussed, among other issues, the humanitarian crisis in Venezuela that has sent an estimated 1.14 million refugees into neighboring Colombia."}},{"is":"video-inline","props":{"type":"video","title":"Report: Venezuela part of bigger US push to have more influence in region","caption":"National security adviser John Bolton recently called Venezuela, Cuba and Nicaragua the 'troika of tyranny' and predicted 'the troika will crumble'; reaction and analysis from A.B. Stoddard, associate editor at Real Clear Politics.","videoId":"5997056800001","imageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fmedia2.foxnews.com\u002FBrightCove\u002F694940094001\u002F2019\u002F01\u002F31\u002F694940094001_5997064078001_5997056800001-vs.jpg","originalImageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fmedia2.foxnews.com\u002FBrightCove\u002F694940094001\u002F2019\u002F01\u002F31\u002F694940094001_5997064078001_5997056800001-vs.jpg","url":"http:\u002F\u002Fvideo.foxnews.com\u002Fv\u002F5997056800001","videoDomain":"foxnews"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Following the meeting, Trump remained coy about the possibility of sending troops to Venezuela &#x2013; only noting a number of options are available if Maduro does not step down from power."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"&#x201C;I always have a plan B, and C, and D, and E and F,&#x201D; Trump said. &#x201C;A lot of things are happening in Venezuela that people don&apos;t know about, there&apos;s a lot of support for what we&apos;re doing, tremendous support.&#x201D;"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Despite having the world&apos;s largest oil reserves, Venezuela is gripped by widespread malnutrition, disease and violence after 20 years of socialist rule launched by the late President Hugo Chavez. Critics accuse Maduro, Chavez&apos;s hand-picked successor, of unfairly winning an election last year for a second six-year term by banning his popular rivals from running and jailing others."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The U.S. and other nations want Maduro to step down and have recognized National Assembly leader Guaido as Venezuela&apos;s rightful leader. Venezuelans have also staged large protests to pressure Maduro to leave."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.foxnews.com\u002Fapps-products\" target=\"_blank\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGET THE FOX NEWS APP\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Venezuela&apos;s opposition has called its supporters into the streets across the country in a campaign to break the military&apos;s support of Maduro, while Maduro is rallying supporters to demonstrations following more than a month of pressure led by Guaido."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"&quot;Right now, I&apos;m going to give this order to the armed forces: Allow in the humanitarian aid. That&apos;s an order,&quot; Guaido told the mass of people gathered in Caracas."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The struggle now centers on emergency food and medicine from the United States warehoused on the Colombian border town of Cucuta."}},{"is":"video-inline","props":{"type":"video","title":"Key European countries officially recognize Juan Guaido as Venezuela's interim president","caption":"President Nicolas Maduro rejects ultimatum by European countries to call for new elections; Benjamin Hall reports from London.","videoId":"5998322177001","imageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fmedia2.foxnews.com\u002FBrightCove\u002F694940094001\u002F2019\u002F02\u002F04\